      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model physics must adequately represent the dominant mechanics of ASTM F1717 compression-bending for a metallic pedicle screw construct.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material model for Ti-6Al-4V is appropriate for pre-yield regime QoIs (stiffness). Bilinear isotropic hardening captures post-yield behavior for yield force and 40 mm displacement QoIs. Frictional contact at screw-rod interface (mu=0.2) validated against published tribological data. Large-displacement formulation activated."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material and geometric inputs must be traceable to measured or certified values with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and tangent modulus (2.1 GPa) sourced from ASTM F136 certificates of conformance for the production lot. Geometric dimensions measured from CMM inspection of test articles (n=5 per lot). Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo sampling (n=500 runs)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test specimens must be representative of the production design and lot; traceability to device history records required.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested, drawn from a single production lot with full device history records. UHMWPE blocks and titanium rods sourced per ASTM F1717 specification. Specimen dimensions verified by CMM prior to testing. Sample size sufficient to characterize inter-specimen variability."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span the range of conditions relevant to the COU, or deviations must be justified.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single axial offset (50 mm) per ASTM F1717. The COU is limited to this standard configuration; however, only one test condition was evaluated, which limits generalizability to other offsets. This factor is below the required level and is documented as an accepted limitation given that the regulatory submission is restricted to the F1717-standard configuration."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs must be demonstrably equivalent to the physical test conditions, including geometry, material, boundary conditions, and loading.",
      "rationale": "FEA geometry reconstructed from CAD nominal dimensions with CMM-measured deviations applied as perturbations. Boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture kinematics (pin-pin, 50 mm offset). Material inputs matched to lot-specific certificates. Loading ramp rate in FEA matched quasi-static experimental rate (1 mm/min equivalent)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 and percent QoI difference < 10% for all three QoIs.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy both acceptance criteria across the three-institution FEA ensemble. Maximum E/uval observed was 1.22 (yield force, Lab 2 data). Maximum percent difference was 3.5%. Validation uncertainty uval computed per ASME V&V 20 combining experimental measurement uncertainty and FEA numerical uncertainty."
    },
